// test-error
// MISRA C:2012 Rule 10.4 (ADR-024, Issue #1091): a binary operator may not
// combine operands of different essential type category. `u32 + i32` mixes
// unsigned and signed, so it must be a compile error; reinterpret one operand
// with bit indexing (e.g. `b[0, 32]`) to combine them explicitly.
u32 main() {
    u32 a <- 1;
    i32 b <- 2;
    u32 c <- a + b;
    return 0;
}
